<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-15T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/807</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Tiflis</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-15T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            15, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your telegrams December 4, 9 p.m., and subsequent dates including
                                December 13, 6 p.m., received. Department appreciates your thorough
                                reports on situation, is in touch with Allied Governments, and hopes
                                to give you definite instructions shortly on whole subject.
                                Meanwhile do not commit this Government. No country either
                                belligerent or neutral has recognized Bolshevik government,
                                Petrograd.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>[For a description of the development of the anti-Bolshevik
                                    movement of the Cossacks under <persName corresp="#p_KGAM1">Kaledin</persName> during the first days of December 1917,
                                    see despatch No. 212 of December 15, 1917, from the Consul
                                    General at Moscow, <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_304">Volume
                                        I, page 304</ref>.]</p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>